caption.text:
2021 is knocking at the door.

So if you are starting in 2021. Here my suggestion for you.

I know a lot of people will suggest you something else.

But my suggestions for 2021 is like this. I'll explain why.

First TypeScript, because TypeScript is taking more than half JavaScript World. Learning TypeScript will lead you into a lot of jobs. JS/TS has the most job in the world current now.

Then 2nd one is python. It's a beast, By knowing python you can work almost any sector in computer science. Like - machine learning, web development, robotics, software engineer, automated testing etc.

Third one is rust. Rust doesnt have lots of job, also currently rust developers are not huge. So if you are good at it, then you'll get job easily.

Fourth is golang, this language can be used as cloud functions, highly scalable sever and many more. Learning it can lead big salaries job!

Fifth one is swift, for making good iOS app you need to learn swift. It's mac based thing and if you become good with it then it's easier to make more money than android developers.

Now choice is yours. 

Feel free to learn anything because everything has jobs.

But become good with it.

Any question?

caption.text:
↗️ To będzie popularne w kolejnych miesiącach.

Kierunki rozwoju programowania są trochę nieobliczalne. Ale postanowiłem prześledzić, co się dzieje teraz i przewidzieć przyszłość 🔮

Co będzie popularne w tym roku?
✅ Web3 - jesteśmy na początku drogi do czegoś nowego. Możliwości jakie daje Web3 spowodują, że ktoś wymyśli jak pozbyć się aktualnych problemów. Może za 5-10 lat ale warto już teraz obserwować.
✅ Rust - Rust coraz mocniej wchodzi w świat JS. Obstawiam, że za chwilę cały ekosystem deweloperski JS będzie stał na Rust
✅ WebAssembly - przy specyficznych projektach WASM daje potężny wzrost wydajności.
✅ Mikrofrontendy - wraz z pojawieniem się Module Federation mikrofrontendy zyskują na popularności. I za chwilę to może być tak samo normalne jak mikroserwisy teraz.
✅ SSR & SSG - wracamy do roziwązań dających lepsze SEO. I nie tracimy przy tym możliwości UI/UX znanych z SPA
✅ Security - tematów związanych z bezpieczeństwem jest coraz więcej i czas się zacząć uczyć jak tworzyć bezpieczne aplikacje
✅ A11y - czyli strony internetowe dla każdego. A tak między nami - to jest całkiem niezła nisza biznesowa do zagospodarowania.

Co o tym sądzisz? Zgadzasz się czy masz zupełnie inne typy. Podziel się w komentarzu - chętnie podyskutuję, co nasz czeka w przyszłości.

Por que saber sobre Design Patterns é importante? 

Conhecer Design Patterns é algo de extrema importância no desenvolvimento de qualquer software. A utilização desses padrões nos ajuda a desenvolver de forma mais rápida frente a desafios semelhantes, fornece uma linguagem comum durante a documentação e discussões técnicas além de nos auxiliar a organizar o código fonte do software que estamos desenvolvendo.

caption.text:
Other than getting some rest and taking care of your mental and physical health during the weekend, when you think of yourself — what does the self enjoy doing when you’re not thinking about your daily responsibilities, desires, goals. What do you enjoy doing when you’re unaware of the time you spend? What comes to your mind? Think about the hobbies you’ve always wanted to give time to! 

•••

“What the smartest people do on the weekend is what everyone else will do during the week in ten years.” — dixon.org

- “Today, the tech hobbies with momentum include math-based currencies like Bitcoin….”

•••

I’m doing the fun work! “The fun” for me stands for all the readings and note-takings of things I want to gain more knowledge about. What I’m reading currently is: “Why decentralization matters” by cdixon, and I’ll continue to listen to the latest podcast of @timferriss. I already took some keyword notes on Social and Smart contracts, where Smart contracts are linked to the digital world, and Social contracts are connected to the real world. 

••• 

I guess my Instagram will turn into a note-keeping app for me, and I’m happy about it! 🐝🌸

•••
